    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix MCS selection mismatch in UL node synchronization handling\n\n### Summary\nThe VNF UL node synchronization handler was using incorrect timing calculations when operating in NR mode. This caused downstream MCS selection to mismatch channel quality reports and UE capabilities.\n\nThe root cause was that `vnf_handle_ul_node_sync` always used LTE-specific timing constants (`NFAPI_MAX_SFNSFDEC`) even when processing NR messages. This led to incorrect latency calculations that propagated to scheduling decisions.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf_p7.c`: Updated `vnf_handle_ul_node_sync` to detect NR context via `phy->mu` and use appropriate timing constants\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf_p7.c`: Fixed wrap-around calculations for `t1`/`t2` timestamps  \n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf_p7.c`: Corrected time unit conversions from microseconds to slot/subframe boundaries\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder high traffic loads with mixed LTE/NR PNFs, observe MCS selection that doesn't match reported CQI values. UE throughput may drop significantly due to mismatched modulation schemes. Trace logs show timing deltas that exceed expected propagation delays.\n\n"
}